  "title": "Full Stack Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>About fileAI</strong></p>\n<p>fileAI leverages proprietary AI to process any file end-to-end directly into any system without manual intervention. By streamlining repetitive workflows, fileAI enables your team to focus on higher-value tasks and boost productivity.</p>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Build and maintain core features across our SaaS platform using React, TypeScript, and Node.js</li>\n  <li>Design, develop, and document RESTful APIs to support frontend functionality</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with design, product, and other engineers to define and deliver user-facing features</li>\n  <li>Write clean, maintainable, and testable code</li>\n  <li>Participate in code reviews and architecture discussions</li>\n  <li>Contribute to DevOps, CI/CD pipelines, and infrastructure decisions (bonus if you have experience with AWS or similar)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Proven experience in software development</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in React and TypeScript</li>\n  <li>Solid experience with Node.js and backend development</li>\n  <li>Strong understanding of RESTful API design principles</li>\n  <li>Familiarity with relational databases (PostgreSQL preferred)</li>\n  <li>Experience with version control tools (Git) and CI/CD pipelines</li>\n  <li>Excellent communication skills and a team-first mentality</li>\n  <li>Bonus: Experience in SaaS, DevOps, testing frameworks, or performance optimization</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p><strong>Perks &amp; Culture</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Competitive salary and performance-based incentives.</li>\n  <li>Health insurance, lunch perks, uncapped leave.</li>\n  <li>Dynamic and collaborative work environment.</li>\n  <li>Grow &amp; learn with a fast-growing organization.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><br></p>\n<p>Please submit your application via this form: <a href=\"https://forms.gle/GfcR3juEaeidQYm98\"><u>https://forms.gle/GfcR3juEaeidQYm98</u></a></p>",
